I love this location. We have a standing Thursday order of 15 to 20 orders since 2015 and they rock them out like it's nothing. <userid>106371127795143709687</userid><Name>David Thomas< /Name><date>1506551594825<//date>< Rating>
5< /Rating>
<review>This has always been an exceptionally well run establishment.  The building is historic, note the handsome wooden rafters on the ceiling.  It used to be a bank back in the good old days.  Of course, I was chagrined when this Starbucks opened up catty-corner to my then favorite (and all-night) coffeehouse Lestat's.

BUT, the coffee is better here, and the food too.  It is air conditioned nicely and the music is hip and varied enough to continue making an impression.

There is nice outdoor seating too, technically now all non-smoking, but if you are by your self out there, and discrete, you can puff a couple now and then.

I can't think of a better run Starbucks, even a better run business than this particular Starbucks frachise.  Kudos to the owners, the management, and of course the hard-working staff!  Tip big--it is how you can best stimulate the economy, generally speaking!!!</review><pics>None</pics><Response>None</Response><gmap_id>0x80d954548eea9167:0xb4e774333c9d3333</gmap_id></record>

<text>Terrible experience.  I highly recommend using a more reputable and established rental service.  I arrived at the San Diego aiport and navigated my way to the rental car shuttle area.  After sitting for about 10 minutes watching the other shuttles for the other companies come and go I eventually called the E-Z office; however, there was no answer.  After 3 more calls with no answer I had to call the 1-800 reservation line and they eventually connected me through to the office.  I was then informed that there is not shuttle that comes by at regular intervals but that I was supposed to call and request the shuttle.  The shuttle arrived about 20 minutes later.  The shuttle was not a bus like the other companies but was instead a dirty cargo van with seats.  I was then driven far away from the airport to the dirty run-down rental office.

At that point I was asked if I wouldn't mind driving one of their minivans.  I declined and stated that I would prefer to drive the vehicle that I had reserved.  (That was, not surprisingly, the reason that I reserved it!)  I was then told that the only vehicle available was a minivan.  Since it took so long to actually get to the office I did not have time to go to another company so I accepted the minivan.

Then the rental agent informed me that the tank had not been topped off.  Nevertheless she told me that I had to initial a portion of the rental contract that required me to return the vehicle with a full tank!  Luckily I am a lawyer and I read contracts before I sign them but the average person would probably just have initialled that provision of the contract.  I refused to initial the provision.  This was perhaps the most disturbing part of my experience.  Poor customer service and business management are one thing, but this was an intentional act of dishonesty and manipulation.  Obviously the intent was to take advantage of people who don't read the fine print of the rental contract.  This is not a trustworthy company.

After I refused to initial that portion of the contract I was told that I could take the van anyway.  I had to do a significant amount of driving and incurred extra expense due to driving a van rather than a small sedan.

My overall recommendation is to avoid this company.  It is not worth the headaches.  There are many other choices at the San Diego airport who offer much better customer service and reliability.</text>< Pics>

<name>Brittany TerBush<//name>< review>
DON'T RENT HERE - YOUR THINGS WILL BE STOLEN
I began renting in January. I received a call on May 6th saying my lock was missing and a  new one had been put on - I hadn't been to the unit in months so I requested a photo of the inside: ALL my large boxes of family photos, my expensive camera and electronics, my clothes, my legal documents - ALL GONE. I also was told to file a report with Oakland PD. I did and week later received a call from Napa PD saying some of my things had been found in the possession of a known burglar along with other victims. He had stolen my identity with the documents in the unit. But I also had insurance on the unit so thought I had some protection against the loss, then TODAY I received a letter saying SmartStop saying the insurance claim was denied because according to SmartStop THERE WAS NO PROOF THE UNIT WAS BROKEN INTO. I am heartbroken and angry.

It looks like this happens regularly after reading this other review.
DON'T RENT HERE - YOUR THINGS WILL BE STOLEN< /review>

<Time>1551387784574<//Time><Rating>5<//Rating>< text>
Had an excellent experience w/ this storage place.

For one, DeDe, the front desk manager, is a real asset to the company. She has shown real care and empathy for me as a customer, for instance triple-checking that I was getting the correct discount when I first rented my unit. She even got on the phone with the driver of the truck I was expecting and advocated on my behalf to actually get them to commit to a delivery time -- this was a rare bright spot in an otherwise chaotic day.

In terms of the storage place itself, it features ground floor units and easy access. A tractor-trailer was able to park next to my unit, for instance. Also, I felt like they take security really seriously, with DeDe being really eagled-eyed about preventing any tailgating or other kinds of unauthorized access.<//text>

<user_id>110612938287590858436< /user_id><name>Michael Magtira< /name>< time>
1519699945686</time>
< Rating>
5</Rating>
<review>I had a sharp object punctured the left rear tire of my VW and I was unable to change the tire myself because the lock on the rim was stripped. So, I called the the dealership (VW in Alhambra) and they were going to charge me $140 per lock. That's more than $500 and it doesn't even involve fixing the tires. Then I remember that I always go to El Dorado to install tires for my other car. I spoke to Lauro and he was very friendly and knowledgeable regarding all my questions. He gave it to me straight that he was not the mechanic and that he wouldn't be able to help. He then suggest to take the car before they open so the mechanic can take a look at the tires. He gave me a quote of $15 depending on the severity of the damage on the lock. So I took the car this morning around 0800. I had it towed because it wasn't drivable. They took care of the car right away and was very helpful. They explain to me that they will have to drill the bolt out and there is a possibly of damaging or scratching the rim. I said it was ok. They were able to take all the bolt out and replace it with the new locks I've purchased online. They made it look easy and my rim wasn't even damaged at all. The charge was $40 for drilling out all 5 lock and fixing the patching the tire. Compare $40 to $560. I saved $520 + tax. I'd take that any day. I wanna give a shout out to all the boys at El Dorado Tires. Great job and thank you. <text>Probably the best gelateria I've been to in the states since touring thru Italy several years ago. It's family owned and run, and the family has a long history of making gelato in Europe. This is their first and only US location at the moment.

<Review>This review is a continuation of a review that I gave for the San Rafael Safelite....which I gave a horrible review for based on my experience.....feel free to check it out.

After San Rafael Safelite did a terrible job, mislead me about service options and then attempted to schedule me 5 weeks out for a warranty service to replace the faulty glass they installed I called my insurance provider and asked about the Oakland Safelite, as I am currently doing consulting work in Oakland and the vehiclke is there most days.

When I called my insurance provider and let them know what happened in San Rafael they assisted in scheduling Oakland and within less than a week Oakland Safelite showed up...the issue was they tried to use the same glass manufacturer that was already used by San Rafael ....a quick reivew of the glass Oakland Safelite brought showed faults in this replacement windsheild glass as well......so we decided not to install and called the office.

After about 2 weeks of back and forth, Oakland Safelite got permission to install the originally requested OEM glass.  The manager at the Oakland facility was timely, helpful and did what she said she would.

The technician, Robert was skilled in his trade and enjoyable to work with.

Overall I give them a 4 of 5 rating as there were some small issues which were resolved quickly.

Long and short of this is ....be careful about the standard glass Safelite is using....it is a cheaper Chinese manufactured glass and in the case of my Porsche Macan, the glass had defects in it and the defects seem to be through the entire production run....I am not sure if this is happening for other car models.....i can tell you it was noticeable around the lower 1/4 of the glass.....a defenite warp that distorted the view.

The folks at the Oakland shop were dillegent, helpful and cooperative and when all was said and done, I have the replacement glass I wanted.<//Review>< Resp>

<Rating>4</Rating><Review>CASH ONLY but they are fast, tasty, and a great value. I wish they were open on Sundays! Would be ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê if they had longer hours and were open on Sundays.

Typical tacqueria style value super tacos & super burritos with your choice of meat. Personally, I like their chicken, but the pork & carne asada are good too. FYI: Hot sauce/salsa is kept in squease bottles in the fridge (along with a selection of Mexican sodas). The red salsa is spicier than the salsa verde. They also use only corn tortillas for the tacos, which makes them a good gluten-free option.

Located in that ancient run-down parking lot on Bascom still bearing the name "Dick's Center." They're easy to overlook. Due to their location on the corner of the strip, the glare from the sun can be quite daunting at certain times of day, but many customers seem to grab food to-go, as there are only a few tables indoors and a few tables outdoors anyway.< /Review>< Pictures>

< date>

<rate>5</rate><text>I'm the kind of person who will NEVER order Tacos when I'm out to eat Mexican food. Chimichangas, Burritos, Fajitas, Tortas, Tostadas, Flautas... literally anything sounds better to me than a Taco. And I've tried every item on the Tacos Mexicos menu.

The verdict: Get the tacos. They are so much better than any other item on the menu and the best value at $3 (veggie super tacos are $2.70). They jam pack the super tacos with filling (a high ratio of meat). The cheese is melted in between the tortillas. Make sure you ask to get them extra crispy for a crunchy outside and soft inside you won't be able to resist. My particular favorite is the BBQ Pork. Haven't stomached the beef tongue or pork cheeks (those just sound too weird to me) and haven't tried the chile relleno, but I'd say the BBQ pork is better than everything else (chicken, carnitas, carne asada).

Trust me -- I know you like burritos and tortas, but I've been in that same predicament... I've gotten those just to try something new and every time have immediately regretted not just getting two super tacos for nearly the same price. There's a reason it's called Tacos Mexicos. Get the tacos.< /text><pictures>None< /pictures><Response>None<//Response>< GmapID>
0x808e34cf3e47c911:0x4e879046e3591d27</GmapID>

< review>
OVERALL: nice venue that's no longer state-of-the-art; parking can be better.

We attended a semi-pro performance (leased event) at the center.  The sound system had issues, and the AC was inadequate to keep a full audience comfortable.

Other than that, the building was well maintained, and the restrooms were clean.  The parking is not very good.  The lot is in bad need of repair and the faded lines are very narrow.< /review>

< text>
This park is a great little pit stop on the way to or coming back from the beach. It is just off the pier at the top of the stairs down to the sand. It wasn't crowded at all, on the weekday, in the AM that me and my guys went. I don't want to give away my secrets, but early is optimal at most places.

The cement slide that runs parallel to the stairs is a great addition.< /text>

This is such a fun beach and town. I visited while passing through on a road trip and am so glad I did! It‚Äôs definitely worth the stop.

The pier is a must walk, as it offers some GORGEOUS views! The town offers so much charm- people out and about with their kids and/or dogs just enjoying life. It‚Äôs fun to be out and about! There‚Äôs a free parking lot within walkable distance to the beach, as well as a pay to park lot. Amble restrooms are available. If your dates are flexible I would advise visiting during the weekday, as the weekend is PACKED!!!!! but regardless of what day you visit, you‚Äôre in for a good time.< /Review>

< user_name>
Gene Waring</user_name>
<time>1601515149819< /time><rate>5</rate><Text>Pismo Beach is a wonderful Mediterranean weathered place to visit! There are many hidden beaches that one may enjoy with few if any other people around. There are a variety of wineries to also visit along with some waterfalls that you can swim at and Lake Lopez where you can camp and wakeboard. Kayaking is also very beautiful with some caves that you can go through at Shell Beach. Don't miss the many miles of sand dunes that you can wander through south of Oceano. It is a wonderful place to see a beautiful sunset dropping into the blue jeweled Waters. Having lived here for 30 years I have been fortunate enough to experience all of the area's Many Wonders and would be happy to help others to find some of these secret places! Have you ever heard of the Dunites? They were an incredible people living in the Dunes that had a tremendous effect on the twentieth century yet no one knows about them anymore. Find out more on Instagram: @the_dunites_Utopia.</Text>< pics>

<time>1577748309674</time><Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
Nice, family friendly beach. Water was ok in December... Warm enough for some people to swim in (if you have a high tolerance for cold water). This beach is also a popular place for surfing, and there is a shop that sells surfer gear close by. The beach is clean, beautiful and long. There are several hotels close by and so many restaurants within walking distance. Parking can be a bit of a hassle the closer you get to the beach front, especially at popular times in the year.</Review>

<Gmap_id>0x80ec58dd2114a2bb:0x9e91d036f9dc6e< /Gmap_id>< user_name>
Joseph Marrs<//user_name>
< text>
I love Pismo Beach, and I've been coming here since before I could walk. Now with stores, restraunts, and parking being open the feel is like an escape to pre-COVID times. They're currently renovating the whole area surrounding the pier (new bathrooms, a park, slides down to the beach, tables, cornhole, etc.) And their new additions look amazing. They finally reopened parking near Wooly's at the end of Pomeroy which really helps with the flow of traffic. The beach is always clean, and it's a great place to hang out with friends, family, pets, or just go for a peaceful walk on your own. The one drawback is the sheer amount of people who smoke marijuana while walking down the street or on the beach; you literally can not escape the smell if you're anywhere near large groups of people. Otherwise it's great, and I'll definitely be back soon.</text>

1593042500705</Time>

<Text>Alder said once it is completed, the hotel will feature a restaurant, pool and event lawn with fire pits and other amenities.

"It's very much a Central Coast beach cottage style," he said. "We didn't look to import Los Angeles to Pismo Beach. Obviously, we like Pismo Beach a lot. It should be a really nice getaway from the hustle and bustle of the major cities -- or the heat of the Central Valley, if that's what you're concerned about."

The hotel is expected to open in April or May 2019, Alder said.

"It's taken us a while to get going, but we're really excited," he said. "It's going to be very high-quality."< /Text><pics>None</pics><resp>None<//resp>< gmap_id>

<username>EM<//username>< date>
1573950430887< /date>
< rate>
5</rate>
< review>
I live down in Los Angeles but would never miss a trip up here with my family every summer. Gorgeous blue water and soft golden sand, with fun rocks to climb on and public activities on one side of the beach, to a quiet and mellow walk on the other. The waves are amazing and I love boogie-boarding in the ocean, no way would I stay down in LA to go surfing. The locals are so friendly, and to top it all off it has that old beach town vibe with buildings that haven't been renovated and modernized like the beaches near me.< /review>

< Review>
Early morning dolphins and whales were very active.  The whales were jumping out of the water making huge splashes,  and some of the dolphins were actually riding the waves. It was the most spectacular site to see.  The beaches are clean and run for miles ready for families to enjoy.  The beaches are also frequently patrolled by police and life guards which really makes it feel safe.</Review>
